{
  "stem": "22047.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I took a contingent of troops aboard this big troop ship in New York Harbor from Camp Kilmer, which was our processing center then.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Aboard this troop ship, I had 20 or so folks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we got our area of the ship readied for the rest of the troops from A Company or from the battalion to come aboard, and I got seasick sitting in the harbor.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] But that was a blessing in disguise because we were on the high seas on Thanksgiving Day, and I was all over my sickness, and everybody else was sick, so we had food galore for Thanksgiving dinner.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was-- ship was called the Americas.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It had been a German luxury liner, and it had been either sold or commandeered by-- I guess it was sold to the United States, and became a troop ship.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was called The Americas.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was quite a big ship.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I went to the 42nd.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I was-- I was sure that I'd be in combat when I went to Fort Benning.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The whole idea was to-- to get a commission and join a unit.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the whole idea.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course when I went to Oklahoma, I knew that it was only a matter of time that we'd be going-- I didn't know then whether we'd be going to the South Pacific or to Europe.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I felt very fortunate that we went to Europe, because we are fighting an enemy that we understood more than we understood the Japanese.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I-- I was pretty sure I'd be going, in-- in 40-- early '42, I was sure of it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because I was going to OCS for-- eventually, to go into combat.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Apprehensive.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
